52 //*********************
53 //Operand collector (OC) modelling (Syed Gilani)
54 //*********************
55 //The OCs are modelled similar to the GPGPU-Sim v3.x documentation and
56 //nVIDIA patents.
57 //the OC need the following GPGPU-Sim config options:
58 //-gpgpu_num_reg_banks 8 # Number of register banks (default = 8)
59 //-gpgpu_reg_bank_use_warp_id 0 # Use warp ID in mapping registers to banks (default = off)
60 //-gpgpu_operand_collector_num_units_sp 6 # number of collector units (default = 4)
61 //-gpgpu_operand_collector_num_units_sfu 8 # number of collector units (default = 4)
62 //-gpgpu_operand_collector_num_units_mem 2 # number of collector units (default = 2)
63 //-gpgpu_operand_collector_num_units_gen 0 # number of collector units (default = 0)
64 //-gpgpu_operand_collector_num_in_ports_sp 1 # number of collector unit in ports (default = 1)
65 //-gpgpu_operand_collector_num_in_ports_sfu 1 # number of collector unit in ports (default = 1)
66 //-gpgpu_operand_collector_num_in_ports_mem 1 # number of collector unit in ports (default = 1)
67 //-gpgpu_operand_collector_num_in_ports_gen 0 # number of collector unit in ports (default = 0)
68 //-gpgpu_operand_collector_num_out_ports_sp 1 # number of collector unit in ports (default = 1)
69 //-gpgpu_operand_collector_num_out_ports_sfu 1 # number of collector unit in ports (default = 1)
70 //-gpgpu_operand_collector_num_out_ports_mem 1 # number of collector unit in ports (default = 1)
71 //-gpgpu_operand_collector_num_out_ports_gen 0 # number of collector unit in ports (default = 0)
72 
73 //The total number of collector units and their input ports, and the number of register file banks
74 //determine the crossbar size.

76 InstFetchU::InstFetchU(ParseXML* XML_interface, int ithCore_, InputParameter* interface_ip_, const CoreDynParam & dyn_p_, bool exist_)
77 :XML(XML_interface),
78  ithCore(ithCore_),
79  interface_ip(*interface_ip_),
80  coredynp(dyn_p_),
81  IB (0),
82  BTB (0),
83  ID_inst (0),
84  ID_operand (0),
85  ID_misc (0),
86  exist(exist_)
87 {
88  if (!exist) return;
89  int idx, tag, data, size, line, assoc, banks;
90  bool debug= false, is_default = true;
91 
92  clockRate = coredynp.clockRate;
93  executionTime = coredynp.executionTime;
94 
95  cache_p = (Cache_policy)XML->sys.core[ithCore].icache.icache_config[7];
96  //Assuming all L1 caches are virtually idxed physically tagged.
97  //cache
98 
99  size = (int)XML->sys.core[ithCore].icache.icache_config[0];
100  line = (int)XML->sys.core[ithCore].icache.icache_config[1];
101  assoc = (int)XML->sys.core[ithCore].icache.icache_config[2];
102  banks = (int)XML->sys.core[ithCore].icache.icache_config[3];
103  idx = debug?9:int(ceil(log2(size/line/assoc)));
104  tag = debug?51:(int)XML->sys.physical_address_width-idx-int(ceil(log2(line))) + EXTRA_TAG_BITS;
105  interface_ip.specific_tag = 1;
106  interface_ip.tag_w = tag;
107  interface_ip.cache_sz = debug?32768:(int)XML->sys.core[ithCore].icache.icache_config[0];
108  interface_ip.line_sz = debug?64:(int)XML->sys.core[ithCore].icache.icache_config[1];
109  interface_ip.assoc = debug?8:(int)XML->sys.core[ithCore].icache.icache_config[2];
110  interface_ip.nbanks = debug?1:(int)XML->sys.core[ithCore].icache.icache_config[3];
111  interface_ip.out_w = interface_ip.line_sz*8;
112  interface_ip.access_mode = 0;//debug?0:XML->sys.core[ithCore].icache.icache_config[5];
113  interface_ip.throughput = debug?1.0/clockRate:XML->sys.core[ithCore].icache.icache_config[4]/clockRate;
114  interface_ip.latency = debug?3.0/clockRate:XML->sys.core[ithCore].icache.icache_config[5]/clockRate;
115  interface_ip.is_cache = true;
116  interface_ip.pure_cam = false;
117  interface_ip.pure_ram = false;
118  // interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_energy = 0;
119  // interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_power = 0;
120  // interface_ip.obj_func_leak_power = 0;
121  // interface_ip.obj_func_cycle_t = 1;
122  interface_ip.num_rw_ports = debug?1:XML->sys.core[ithCore].number_instruction_fetch_ports;
123  interface_ip.num_rd_ports = 0;
124  interface_ip.num_wr_ports = 0;
125  interface_ip.num_se_rd_ports = 0;
126  icache.caches = new ArrayST(&interface_ip, "icache", Core_device, coredynp.opt_local, coredynp.core_ty);
127  scktRatio = g_tp.sckt_co_eff;
128  chip_PR_overhead = g_tp.chip_layout_overhead;
129  macro_PR_overhead = g_tp.macro_layout_overhead;
130  icache.area.set_area(icache.area.get_area()+ icache.caches->local_result.area);
131  area.set_area(area.get_area()+ icache.caches->local_result.area);
132  //output_data_csv(icache.caches.local_result);
133 
134 
135  /*
136  *iCache controllers
137  *miss buffer Each MSHR contains enough state
138  *to handle one or more accesses of any type to a single memory line.
139  *Due to the generality of the MSHR mechanism,
140  *the amount of state involved is non-trivial:
141  *including the address, pointers to the cache entry and destination register,
142  *written data, and various other pieces of state.
143  */
144  interface_ip.num_search_ports = debug?1:XML->sys.core[ithCore].number_instruction_fetch_ports;
145  tag = XML->sys.physical_address_width + EXTRA_TAG_BITS;
146  data = (XML->sys.physical_address_width) + int(ceil(log2(size/line))) + icache.caches->l_ip.line_sz*8;
147  interface_ip.specific_tag = 1;
148  interface_ip.tag_w = tag;
149  interface_ip.line_sz = int(ceil(data/8.0));//int(ceil(pow(2.0,ceil(log2(data)))/8.0));
150  interface_ip.cache_sz = XML->sys.core[ithCore].icache.buffer_sizes[0]*interface_ip.line_sz;
151  interface_ip.assoc = 0;
152  interface_ip.nbanks = 1;
153  interface_ip.out_w = interface_ip.line_sz*8;
154  interface_ip.access_mode = 0;
155  interface_ip.throughput = debug?1.0/clockRate:XML->sys.core[ithCore].icache.icache_config[4]/clockRate;//means cycle time
156  interface_ip.latency = debug?1.0/clockRate:XML->sys.core[ithCore].icache.icache_config[5]/clockRate;//means access time
157  interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_energy = 0;
158  interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_power = 0;
159  interface_ip.obj_func_leak_power = 0;
160  interface_ip.obj_func_cycle_t = 1;
161  interface_ip.num_rw_ports = debug?1:XML->sys.core[ithCore].number_instruction_fetch_ports;
162  interface_ip.num_rd_ports = 0;
163  interface_ip.num_wr_ports = 0;
164  interface_ip.num_se_rd_ports = 0;
165  interface_ip.num_search_ports = XML->sys.core[ithCore].number_instruction_fetch_ports;
166  icache.missb = new ArrayST(&interface_ip, "icacheMissBuffer", Core_device, coredynp.opt_local, coredynp.core_ty);
167  icache.area.set_area(icache.area.get_area()+ icache.missb->local_result.area);
168  area.set_area(area.get_area()+ icache.missb->local_result.area);
169  //output_data_csv(icache.missb.local_result);
170 
171  //fill buffer
172  tag = XML->sys.physical_address_width + EXTRA_TAG_BITS;
173  data = icache.caches->l_ip.line_sz;
174  interface_ip.specific_tag = 1;
175  interface_ip.tag_w = tag;
176  interface_ip.line_sz = data;//int(pow(2.0,ceil(log2(data))));
177  interface_ip.cache_sz = data*XML->sys.core[ithCore].icache.buffer_sizes[1];
178  interface_ip.assoc = 0;
179  interface_ip.nbanks = 1;
180  interface_ip.out_w = interface_ip.line_sz*8;
181  interface_ip.access_mode = 0;
182  interface_ip.throughput = debug?1.0/clockRate:XML->sys.core[ithCore].icache.icache_config[4]/clockRate;
183  interface_ip.latency = debug?1.0/clockRate:XML->sys.core[ithCore].icache.icache_config[5]/clockRate;
184  interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_energy = 0;
185  interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_power = 0;
186  interface_ip.obj_func_leak_power = 0;
187  interface_ip.obj_func_cycle_t = 1;
188  interface_ip.num_rw_ports = debug?1:XML->sys.core[ithCore].number_instruction_fetch_ports;
189  interface_ip.num_rd_ports = 0;
190  interface_ip.num_wr_ports = 0;
191  interface_ip.num_se_rd_ports = 0;
192  interface_ip.num_search_ports = XML->sys.core[ithCore].number_instruction_fetch_ports;
193  icache.ifb = new ArrayST(&interface_ip, "icacheFillBuffer", Core_device, coredynp.opt_local, coredynp.core_ty);
194  icache.area.set_area(icache.area.get_area()+ icache.ifb->local_result.area);
195  area.set_area(area.get_area()+ icache.ifb->local_result.area);
196  //output_data_csv(icache.ifb.local_result);
197 
198  //prefetch buffer
199  tag = XML->sys.physical_address_width + EXTRA_TAG_BITS;//check with previous entries to decide wthether to merge.
200  data = icache.caches->l_ip.line_sz;//separate queue to prevent from cache polution.
201  interface_ip.specific_tag = 1;
202  interface_ip.tag_w = tag;
203  interface_ip.line_sz = data;//int(pow(2.0,ceil(log2(data))));
204  interface_ip.cache_sz = XML->sys.core[ithCore].icache.buffer_sizes[2]*interface_ip.line_sz;
205  interface_ip.assoc = 0;
206  interface_ip.nbanks = 1;
207  interface_ip.out_w = interface_ip.line_sz*8;
208  interface_ip.access_mode = 0;
209  interface_ip.throughput = debug?1.0/clockRate:XML->sys.core[ithCore].icache.icache_config[4]/clockRate;
210  interface_ip.latency = debug?1.0/clockRate:XML->sys.core[ithCore].icache.icache_config[5]/clockRate;
211  interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_energy = 0;
212  interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_power = 0;
213  interface_ip.obj_func_leak_power = 0;
214  interface_ip.obj_func_cycle_t = 1;
215  interface_ip.num_rw_ports = debug?1:XML->sys.core[ithCore].number_instruction_fetch_ports;
216  interface_ip.num_rd_ports = 0;
217  interface_ip.num_wr_ports = 0;
218  interface_ip.num_se_rd_ports = 0;
219  interface_ip.num_search_ports = XML->sys.core[ithCore].number_instruction_fetch_ports;
220  icache.prefetchb = new ArrayST(&interface_ip, "icacheprefetchBuffer", Core_device, coredynp.opt_local, coredynp.core_ty);
221  icache.area.set_area(icache.area.get_area()+ icache.prefetchb->local_result.area);
222  area.set_area(area.get_area()+ icache.prefetchb->local_result.area);
223  //output_data_csv(icache.prefetchb.local_result);
224 
225  //Instruction buffer
226  data = XML->sys.core[ithCore].instruction_length*XML->sys.core[ithCore].peak_issue_width;//icache.caches.l_ip.line_sz; //multiple threads timing sharing the instruction buffer.
227  interface_ip.is_cache = false;
228  interface_ip.pure_ram = true;
229  interface_ip.pure_cam = false;
230  interface_ip.line_sz = int(ceil(data/8.0));
231  interface_ip.cache_sz = XML->sys.core[ithCore].number_hardware_threads*XML->sys.core[ithCore].instruction_buffer_size*interface_ip.line_sz>64?
232  XML->sys.core[ithCore].number_hardware_threads*XML->sys.core[ithCore].instruction_buffer_size*interface_ip.line_sz:64;
233  interface_ip.assoc = 1;
234  interface_ip.nbanks = 1;
235  interface_ip.out_w = interface_ip.line_sz*8;
236  interface_ip.access_mode = 0;
237  interface_ip.throughput = 1.0/clockRate;
238  interface_ip.latency = 1.0/clockRate;
239  interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_energy = 0;
240  interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_power = 0;
241  interface_ip.obj_func_leak_power = 0;
242  interface_ip.obj_func_cycle_t = 1;
243  //NOTE: Assuming IB is time slice shared among threads, every fetch op will at least fetch "fetch width" instructions.
244  interface_ip.num_rw_ports = debug?1:XML->sys.core[ithCore].number_instruction_fetch_ports;//XML->sys.core[ithCore].fetch_width;
245  interface_ip.num_rd_ports = 0;
246  interface_ip.num_wr_ports = 0;
247  interface_ip.num_se_rd_ports = 0;
248  IB = new ArrayST(&interface_ip, "InstBuffer", Core_device, coredynp.opt_local, coredynp.core_ty);
249  IB->area.set_area(IB->area.get_area()+ IB->local_result.area);
250  area.set_area(area.get_area()+ IB->local_result.area);
251  //output_data_csv(IB.IB.local_result);
252 
253  // inst_decoder.opcode_length = XML->sys.core[ithCore].opcode_width;
254  // inst_decoder.init_decoder(is_default, &interface_ip);
255  // inst_decoder.full_decoder_power();
256 
257  if (coredynp.predictionW>0)
258  {
259  /*
260  * BTB branch target buffer, accessed during IF stage. Virtually indexed and virtually tagged
261  * It is only a cache without all the buffers in the cache controller since it is more like a
262  * look up table than a cache with cache controller. When access miss, no load from other places
263  * such as main memory (not actively fill the misses), it is passively updated under two circumstances:
264  * 1) when BPT@ID stage finds out current is a taken branch while BTB missed
265  * 2) When BPT@ID stage predicts differently than BTB
266  * 3) When ID stage finds out current instruction is not a branch while BTB had a hit.(mark as invalid)
267  * 4) when EXEU find out wrong target has been provided from BTB.
268  *
269  */
270  size = XML->sys.core[ithCore].BTB.BTB_config[0];
271  line = XML->sys.core[ithCore].BTB.BTB_config[1];
272  assoc = XML->sys.core[ithCore].BTB.BTB_config[2];
273  banks = XML->sys.core[ithCore].BTB.BTB_config[3];
274  idx = debug?9:int(ceil(log2(size/line/assoc)));
275 // tag = debug?51:XML->sys.virtual_address_width-idx-int(ceil(log2(line))) + int(ceil(log2(XML->sys.core[ithCore].number_hardware_threads))) +EXTRA_TAG_BITS;
276  tag = debug?51:XML->sys.virtual_address_width + int(ceil(log2(XML->sys.core[ithCore].number_hardware_threads))) +EXTRA_TAG_BITS;
277  interface_ip.is_cache = true;
278  interface_ip.pure_ram = false;
279  interface_ip.pure_cam = false;
280  interface_ip.specific_tag = 1;
281  interface_ip.tag_w = tag;
282  interface_ip.cache_sz = debug?32768:size;
283  interface_ip.line_sz = debug?64:line;
284  interface_ip.assoc = debug?8:assoc;
285  interface_ip.nbanks = debug?1:banks;
286  interface_ip.out_w = interface_ip.line_sz*8;
287  interface_ip.access_mode = 0;//debug?0:XML->sys.core[ithCore].dcache.dcache_config[5];
288  interface_ip.throughput = debug?1.0/clockRate:XML->sys.core[ithCore].BTB.BTB_config[4]/clockRate;
289  interface_ip.latency = debug?3.0/clockRate:XML->sys.core[ithCore].BTB.BTB_config[5]/clockRate;
290  interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_energy = 0;
291  interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_power = 0;
292  interface_ip.obj_func_leak_power = 0;
293  interface_ip.obj_func_cycle_t = 1;
294  interface_ip.num_rw_ports = 1;
295  interface_ip.num_rd_ports = coredynp.predictionW;
296  interface_ip.num_wr_ports = coredynp.predictionW;
297  interface_ip.num_se_rd_ports = 0;
298  BTB = new ArrayST(&interface_ip, "Branch Target Buffer", Core_device, coredynp.opt_local, coredynp.core_ty);
299  BTB->area.set_area(BTB->area.get_area()+ BTB->local_result.area);
300  area.set_area(area.get_area()+ BTB->local_result.area);
302 
303  BPT = new BranchPredictor(XML, ithCore, &interface_ip,coredynp);
304  area.set_area(area.get_area()+ BPT->area.get_area());
305  }
306 
307  ID_inst = new inst_decoder(is_default, &interface_ip,
308  coredynp.opcode_length, 1/*Decoder should not know how many by itself*/,
309  coredynp.x86,
310  Core_device, coredynp.core_ty);
311 
312  ID_operand = new inst_decoder(is_default, &interface_ip,
313  coredynp.arch_ireg_width, 1,
314  coredynp.x86,
315  Core_device, coredynp.core_ty);
316 
317  ID_misc = new inst_decoder(is_default, &interface_ip,
318  8/* Prefix field etc upto 14B*/, 1,
319  coredynp.x86,
320  Core_device, coredynp.core_ty);
321  //TODO: X86 decoder should decode the inst in cyclic mode under the control of squencer.
322  //So the dynamic power should be multiplied by a few times.
323  area.set_area(area.get_area()+ (ID_inst->area.get_area()
324  +ID_operand->area.get_area()
325  +ID_misc->area.get_area())*coredynp.decodeW);
326 
327 }

330 BranchPredictor::BranchPredictor(ParseXML* XML_interface, int ithCore_, InputParameter* interface_ip_, const CoreDynParam & dyn_p_, bool exist_)
331 :XML(XML_interface),
332  ithCore(ithCore_),
333  interface_ip(*interface_ip_),
334  coredynp(dyn_p_),
335  globalBPT(0),
336  localBPT(0),
337  L1_localBPT(0),
338  L2_localBPT(0),
339  chooser(0),
340  RAS(0),
341  exist(exist_)
342 {
343  /*
344  * Branch Predictor, accessed during ID stage.
345  * McPAT's branch predictor model is the tournament branch predictor used in Alpha 21264,
346  * including global predictor, local two level predictor, and Chooser.
347  * The Branch predictor also includes a RAS (return address stack) for function calls
348  * Branch predictors are tagged by thread ID and modeled as 1-way associative $
349  * However RAS return address stacks are duplicated for each thread.
350  * TODO:Data Width need to be computed more precisely *
351  */
352  if (!exist) return;
353  int tag, data;
354 
355  clockRate = coredynp.clockRate;
356  executionTime = coredynp.executionTime;
357  interface_ip.assoc = 1;
358  interface_ip.pure_cam = false;
359  if (coredynp.multithreaded)
360  {
361 
362  tag = int(log2(coredynp.num_hthreads)+ EXTRA_TAG_BITS);
363  interface_ip.specific_tag = 1;
364  interface_ip.tag_w = tag;
365 
366  interface_ip.is_cache = true;
367  interface_ip.pure_ram = false;
368  }
369  else
370  {
371  interface_ip.is_cache = false;
372  interface_ip.pure_ram = true;
373 
374  }
375  //Global predictor
376  data = int(ceil(XML->sys.core[ithCore].predictor.global_predictor_bits/8.0));
377  interface_ip.line_sz = data;
378  interface_ip.cache_sz = data*XML->sys.core[ithCore].predictor.global_predictor_entries;
379  interface_ip.nbanks = 1;
380  interface_ip.out_w = interface_ip.line_sz*8;
381  interface_ip.access_mode = 2;
382  interface_ip.throughput = 1.0/clockRate;
383  interface_ip.latency = 1.0/clockRate;
384  interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_energy = 0;
385  interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_power = 0;
386  interface_ip.obj_func_leak_power = 0;
387  interface_ip.obj_func_cycle_t = 1;
388  interface_ip.num_rw_ports = 0;
389  interface_ip.num_rd_ports = coredynp.predictionW;
390  interface_ip.num_wr_ports = coredynp.predictionW;
391  interface_ip.num_se_rd_ports = 0;
392  globalBPT = new ArrayST(&interface_ip, "Global Predictor", Core_device, coredynp.opt_local, coredynp.core_ty);
393  globalBPT->area.set_area(globalBPT->area.get_area()+ globalBPT->local_result.area);
394  area.set_area(area.get_area()+ globalBPT->local_result.area);
395 
396  //Local BPT (Level 1)
397  data = int(ceil(XML->sys.core[ithCore].predictor.local_predictor_size[0]/8.0));
398  interface_ip.line_sz = data;
399  interface_ip.cache_sz = data*XML->sys.core[ithCore].predictor.local_predictor_entries;
400  interface_ip.nbanks = 1;
401  interface_ip.out_w = interface_ip.line_sz*8;
402  interface_ip.access_mode = 2;
403  interface_ip.throughput = 1.0/clockRate;
404  interface_ip.latency = 1.0/clockRate;
405  interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_energy = 0;
406  interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_power = 0;
407  interface_ip.obj_func_leak_power = 0;
408  interface_ip.obj_func_cycle_t = 1;
409  interface_ip.num_rw_ports = 0;
410  interface_ip.num_rd_ports = coredynp.predictionW;
411  interface_ip.num_wr_ports = coredynp.predictionW;
412  interface_ip.num_se_rd_ports = 0;
413  L1_localBPT = new ArrayST(&interface_ip, "L1 local Predictor", Core_device, coredynp.opt_local, coredynp.core_ty);
414  L1_localBPT->area.set_area(L1_localBPT->area.get_area()+ L1_localBPT->local_result.area);
415  area.set_area(area.get_area()+ L1_localBPT->local_result.area);
416 
417  //Local BPT (Level 2)
418  data = int(ceil(XML->sys.core[ithCore].predictor.local_predictor_size[1]/8.0));
419  interface_ip.line_sz = data;
420  interface_ip.cache_sz = data*XML->sys.core[ithCore].predictor.local_predictor_entries;
421  interface_ip.nbanks = 1;
422  interface_ip.out_w = interface_ip.line_sz*8;
423  interface_ip.access_mode = 2;
424  interface_ip.throughput = 1.0/clockRate;
425  interface_ip.latency = 1.0/clockRate;
426  interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_energy = 0;
427  interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_power = 0;
428  interface_ip.obj_func_leak_power = 0;
429  interface_ip.obj_func_cycle_t = 1;
430  interface_ip.num_rw_ports = 0;
431  interface_ip.num_rd_ports = coredynp.predictionW;
432  interface_ip.num_wr_ports = coredynp.predictionW;
433  interface_ip.num_se_rd_ports = 0;
434  L2_localBPT = new ArrayST(&interface_ip, "L2 local Predictor", Core_device, coredynp.opt_local, coredynp.core_ty);
435  L2_localBPT->area.set_area(L2_localBPT->area.get_area()+ L2_localBPT->local_result.area);
436  area.set_area(area.get_area()+ L2_localBPT->local_result.area);
437 
438  //Chooser
439  data = int(ceil(XML->sys.core[ithCore].predictor.chooser_predictor_bits/8.0));
440  interface_ip.line_sz = data;
441  interface_ip.cache_sz = data*XML->sys.core[ithCore].predictor.chooser_predictor_entries;
442  interface_ip.nbanks = 1;
443  interface_ip.out_w = interface_ip.line_sz*8;
444  interface_ip.access_mode = 2;
445  interface_ip.throughput = 1.0/clockRate;
446  interface_ip.latency = 1.0/clockRate;
447  interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_energy = 0;
448  interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_power = 0;
449  interface_ip.obj_func_leak_power = 0;
450  interface_ip.obj_func_cycle_t = 1;
451  interface_ip.num_rw_ports = 0;
452  interface_ip.num_rd_ports = coredynp.predictionW;
453  interface_ip.num_wr_ports = coredynp.predictionW;
454  interface_ip.num_se_rd_ports = 0;
455  chooser = new ArrayST(&interface_ip, "Predictor Chooser", Core_device, coredynp.opt_local, coredynp.core_ty);
456  chooser->area.set_area(chooser->area.get_area()+ chooser->local_result.area);
457  area.set_area(area.get_area()+ chooser->local_result.area);
458 
459  //RAS return address stacks are Duplicated for each thread.
460  interface_ip.is_cache = false;
461  interface_ip.pure_ram = true;
462  data = int(ceil(coredynp.pc_width/8.0));
463  interface_ip.line_sz = data;
464  interface_ip.cache_sz = data*XML->sys.core[ithCore].RAS_size;
465  interface_ip.assoc = 1;
466  interface_ip.nbanks = 1;
467  interface_ip.out_w = interface_ip.line_sz*8;
468  interface_ip.access_mode = 2;
469  interface_ip.throughput = 1.0/clockRate;
470  interface_ip.latency = 1.0/clockRate;
471  interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_energy = 0;
472  interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_power = 0;
473  interface_ip.obj_func_leak_power = 0;
474  interface_ip.obj_func_cycle_t = 1;
475  interface_ip.num_rw_ports = 0;
476  interface_ip.num_rd_ports = coredynp.predictionW;
477  interface_ip.num_wr_ports = coredynp.predictionW;
478  interface_ip.num_se_rd_ports = 0;
479  RAS = new ArrayST(&interface_ip, "RAS", Core_device, coredynp.opt_local, coredynp.core_ty);
480  RAS->area.set_area(RAS->area.get_area()+ RAS->local_result.area*coredynp.num_hthreads);
481  area.set_area(area.get_area()+ RAS->local_result.area*coredynp.num_hthreads);
482 
483 }
484 
485 SchedulerU::SchedulerU(ParseXML* XML_interface, int ithCore_, InputParameter* interface_ip_, const CoreDynParam & dyn_p_, bool exist_)
486 :XML(XML_interface),
487  ithCore(ithCore_),
488  interface_ip(*interface_ip_),
489  coredynp(dyn_p_),
490  int_inst_window(0),
491  fp_inst_window(0),
492  ROB(0),
493  instruction_selection(0),
494  exist(exist_)
495  {
496  if (!exist) return;
497  int tag, data;
498  bool is_default=true;
499  string tmp_name;
500 
501  clockRate = coredynp.clockRate;
502  executionTime = coredynp.executionTime;
503  if ((coredynp.core_ty==Inorder && coredynp.multithreaded))
504  {
505  //Instruction issue queue, in-order multi-issue or multithreaded processor also has this structure. Unified window for Inorder processors
506  tag = int(log2(XML->sys.core[ithCore].number_hardware_threads)*coredynp.perThreadState);//This is the normal thread state bits based on Niagara Design
507  data = XML->sys.core[ithCore].instruction_length;
508  //NOTE: x86 inst can be very lengthy, up to 15B. Source: Intel® 64 and IA-32 Architectures
509  //Software Developer’s Manual
510  interface_ip.is_cache = true;
511  interface_ip.pure_cam = false;
512  interface_ip.pure_ram = false;
513  interface_ip.line_sz = int(ceil(data/8.0));
514  interface_ip.specific_tag = 1;
515  interface_ip.tag_w = tag;
516  interface_ip.cache_sz = XML->sys.core[ithCore].instruction_window_size*interface_ip.line_sz>64?XML->sys.core[ithCore].instruction_window_size*interface_ip.line_sz:64;
517  interface_ip.assoc = 0;
518  interface_ip.nbanks = 1;
519  interface_ip.out_w = interface_ip.line_sz*8;
520  interface_ip.access_mode = 1;
521  interface_ip.throughput = 1.0/clockRate;
522  interface_ip.latency = 1.0/clockRate;
523  interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_energy = 0;
524  interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_power = 0;
525  interface_ip.obj_func_leak_power = 0;
526  interface_ip.obj_func_cycle_t = 1;
527  interface_ip.num_rw_ports = 0;
528  interface_ip.num_rd_ports = coredynp.peak_issueW;
529  interface_ip.num_wr_ports = coredynp.peak_issueW;
530  interface_ip.num_se_rd_ports = 0;
531  interface_ip.num_search_ports = coredynp.peak_issueW;
532  int_inst_window = new ArrayST(&interface_ip, "InstFetchQueue", Core_device, coredynp.opt_local, coredynp.core_ty);
533  int_inst_window->area.set_area(int_inst_window->area.get_area()+ int_inst_window->local_result.area*coredynp.num_pipelines);
534  area.set_area(area.get_area()+ int_inst_window->local_result.area*coredynp.num_pipelines);
535  //output_data_csv(iRS.RS.local_result);
536  Iw_height =int_inst_window->local_result.cache_ht;
537 
538  /*
539  * selection logic
540  * In a single-issue Inorder multithreaded processor like Niagara, issue width=1*number_of_threads since the processor does need to pick up
541  * instructions from multiple ready ones(although these ready ones are from different threads).While SMT processors do not distinguish which thread belongs to who
542  * at the issue stage.
543  */
544 
545  instruction_selection = new selection_logic(is_default, XML->sys.core[ithCore].instruction_window_size,
546  coredynp.peak_issueW*XML->sys.core[ithCore].number_hardware_threads,
547  &interface_ip, Core_device, coredynp.core_ty);
548  }
549 
550  if (coredynp.core_ty==OOO)
551  {
552  /*
553  * CAM based instruction window
554  * For physicalRegFilebased OOO it is the instruction issue queue, where only tags of phy regs are stored
555  * For RS based OOO it is the Reservation station, where both tags and values of phy regs are stored
556  * It is written once and read twice(two operands) before an instruction can be issued.
557  * X86 instruction can be very long up to 15B. add instruction length in XML
558  */
559  if(coredynp.scheu_ty==PhysicalRegFile)
560  {
561  tag = coredynp.phy_ireg_width;
562  // Each time only half of the tag is compared, but two tag should be stored.
563  // This underestimate the search power
564  data = int((ceil((coredynp.instruction_length+2*(coredynp.phy_ireg_width - coredynp.arch_ireg_width))/2.0)/8.0));
565  //Data width being divided by 2 means only after both operands available the whole data will be read out.
566  //This is modeled using two equivalent readouts with half of the data width
567  tmp_name = "InstIssueQueue";
568  }
569  else
570  {
571  tag = coredynp.phy_ireg_width;
572  // Each time only half of the tag is compared, but two tag should be stored.
573  // This underestimate the search power
574  data = int(ceil(((coredynp.instruction_length+2*(coredynp.phy_ireg_width - coredynp.arch_ireg_width)+
575  2*coredynp.int_data_width)/2.0)/8.0));
576  //Data width being divided by 2 means only after both operands available the whole data will be read out.
577  //This is modeled using two equivalent readouts with half of the data width
578 
579  tmp_name = "IntReservationStation";
580  }
581  interface_ip.is_cache = true;
582  interface_ip.pure_cam = false;
583  interface_ip.pure_ram = false;
584  interface_ip.line_sz = data;
585  interface_ip.cache_sz = data*XML->sys.core[ithCore].instruction_window_size;
586  interface_ip.assoc = 0;
587  interface_ip.nbanks = 1;
588  interface_ip.out_w = interface_ip.line_sz*8;
589  interface_ip.specific_tag = 1;
590  interface_ip.tag_w = tag;
591  interface_ip.access_mode = 0;
592  interface_ip.throughput = 2*1.0/clockRate;
593  interface_ip.latency = 2*1.0/clockRate;
594  interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_energy = 0;
595  interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_power = 0;
596  interface_ip.obj_func_leak_power = 0;
597  interface_ip.obj_func_cycle_t = 1;
598  interface_ip.num_rw_ports = 0;
599  interface_ip.num_rd_ports = coredynp.peak_issueW;
600  interface_ip.num_wr_ports = coredynp.peak_issueW;
601  interface_ip.num_se_rd_ports = 0;
602  interface_ip.num_search_ports = coredynp.peak_issueW;
603  int_inst_window = new ArrayST(&interface_ip, tmp_name, Core_device, coredynp.opt_local, coredynp.core_ty);
604  int_inst_window->area.set_area(int_inst_window->area.get_area()+ int_inst_window->local_result.area*coredynp.num_pipelines);
605  area.set_area(area.get_area()+ int_inst_window->local_result.area*coredynp.num_pipelines);
606  Iw_height =int_inst_window->local_result.cache_ht;
607  //FU inst window
608  if(coredynp.scheu_ty==PhysicalRegFile)
609  {
610  tag = 2*coredynp.phy_freg_width;// TODO: each time only half of the tag is compared
611  data = int(ceil((coredynp.instruction_length+2*(coredynp.phy_freg_width - coredynp.arch_freg_width))/8.0));
612  tmp_name = "FPIssueQueue";
613  }
614  else
615  {
616  tag = 2*coredynp.phy_ireg_width;
617  data = int(ceil((coredynp.instruction_length+2*(coredynp.phy_freg_width - coredynp.arch_freg_width)+
618  2*coredynp.fp_data_width)/8.0));
619  tmp_name = "FPReservationStation";
620  }
621  interface_ip.is_cache = true;
622  interface_ip.pure_cam = false;
623  interface_ip.pure_ram = false;
624  interface_ip.line_sz = data;
625  interface_ip.cache_sz = data*XML->sys.core[ithCore].fp_instruction_window_size;
626  interface_ip.assoc = 0;
627  interface_ip.nbanks = 1;
628  interface_ip.out_w = interface_ip.line_sz*8;
629  interface_ip.specific_tag = 1;
630  interface_ip.tag_w = tag;
631  interface_ip.access_mode = 0;
632  interface_ip.throughput = 1.0/clockRate;
633  interface_ip.latency = 1.0/clockRate;
634  interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_energy = 0;
635  interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_power = 0;
636  interface_ip.obj_func_leak_power = 0;
637  interface_ip.obj_func_cycle_t = 1;
638  interface_ip.num_rw_ports = 0;
639  interface_ip.num_rd_ports = coredynp.fp_issueW;
640  interface_ip.num_wr_ports = coredynp.fp_issueW;
641  interface_ip.num_se_rd_ports = 0;
642  interface_ip.num_search_ports = coredynp.fp_issueW;
643  fp_inst_window = new ArrayST(&interface_ip, tmp_name, Core_device, coredynp.opt_local, coredynp.core_ty);
644  fp_inst_window->area.set_area(fp_inst_window->area.get_area()+ fp_inst_window->local_result.area*coredynp.num_fp_pipelines);
645  area.set_area(area.get_area()+ fp_inst_window->local_result.area*coredynp.num_fp_pipelines);
646  fp_Iw_height =fp_inst_window->local_result.cache_ht;
647 
648  if (XML->sys.core[ithCore].ROB_size >0)
649  {
650  /*
651  * if ROB_size = 0, then the target processor does not support hardware-based
652  * speculation, i.e. , the processor allow OOO issue as well as OOO completion, which
653  * means branch must be resolved before instruction issued into instruction window, since
654  * there is no change to flush miss-predict branch path after instructions are issued in this situation.
655  *
656  * ROB.ROB size = inflight inst. ROB is unified for int and fp inst.
657  * One old approach is to combine the RAT and ROB as a huge CAM structure as in AMD K7.
658  * However, this approach is abandoned due to its high power and poor scalablility.
659  * McPAT uses current implementation of ROB as circular buffer.
660  * ROB is written once when instruction is issued and read once when the instruction is committed. *
661  */
662  int robExtra = int(ceil(5 + log2(coredynp.num_hthreads)));
663  //5 bits are: busy, Issued, Finished, speculative, valid
664  if(coredynp.scheu_ty==PhysicalRegFile)
665  {
666  //PC is to id the instruction for recover exception.
667  //inst is used to map the renamed dest. registers.so that commit stage can know which reg/RRAT to update
668 // data = int(ceil((robExtra+coredynp.pc_width +
669 // coredynp.instruction_length + 2*coredynp.phy_ireg_width)/8.0));
670  data = int(ceil((robExtra+coredynp.pc_width +
671  coredynp.phy_ireg_width)/8.0));
672  }
673  else
674  {
675  //in RS based OOO, ROB also contains value of destination reg
676 // data = int(ceil((robExtra+coredynp.pc_width +
677 // coredynp.instruction_length + 2*coredynp.phy_ireg_width + coredynp.fp_data_width)/8.0));
678  data = int(ceil((robExtra + coredynp.pc_width +
679  coredynp.phy_ireg_width + coredynp.fp_data_width)/8.0));
680  }
681  interface_ip.is_cache = false;
682  interface_ip.pure_cam = false;
683  interface_ip.pure_ram = true;
684  interface_ip.line_sz = data;
685  interface_ip.cache_sz = data*XML->sys.core[ithCore].ROB_size;//The XML ROB size is for all threads
686  interface_ip.assoc = 1;
687  interface_ip.nbanks = 1;
688  interface_ip.out_w = interface_ip.line_sz*8;
689  interface_ip.access_mode = 1;
690  interface_ip.throughput = 1.0/clockRate;
691  interface_ip.latency = 1.0/clockRate;
692  interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_energy = 0;
693  interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_power = 0;
694  interface_ip.obj_func_leak_power = 0;
695  interface_ip.obj_func_cycle_t = 1;
696  interface_ip.num_rw_ports = 0;
697  interface_ip.num_rd_ports = coredynp.peak_commitW;
698  interface_ip.num_wr_ports = coredynp.peak_issueW;
699  interface_ip.num_se_rd_ports = 0;
700  interface_ip.num_search_ports = 0;
701  ROB = new ArrayST(&interface_ip, "ReorderBuffer", Core_device, coredynp.opt_local, coredynp.core_ty);
702  ROB->area.set_area(ROB->area.get_area()+ ROB->local_result.area*coredynp.num_pipelines);
703  area.set_area(area.get_area()+ ROB->local_result.area*coredynp.num_pipelines);
704  ROB_height =ROB->local_result.cache_ht;
705  }
706 
707  instruction_selection = new selection_logic(is_default, XML->sys.core[ithCore].instruction_window_size,
708  coredynp.peak_issueW, &interface_ip, Core_device, coredynp.core_ty);
709  }
710 }

712 LoadStoreU::LoadStoreU(ParseXML* XML_interface, int ithCore_, InputParameter* interface_ip_, const CoreDynParam & dyn_p_,bool exist_)
713 :XML(XML_interface),
714  ithCore(ithCore_),
715  interface_ip(*interface_ip_),
716  coredynp(dyn_p_),
717  LSQ(0),
718  exist(exist_)
719 {
720  if (!exist) return;
721  int idx, tag, data, size, line, assoc;
722  bool debug= false;
723  int ldst_opcode = XML->sys.core[ithCore].opcode_width;//16;
724 
725  clockRate = coredynp.clockRate;
726  executionTime = coredynp.executionTime;
727  cache_p = (Cache_policy)XML->sys.core[ithCore].dcache.dcache_config[7];
728 
729  interface_ip.num_search_ports = XML->sys.core[ithCore].memory_ports;
730  interface_ip.is_cache = true;
731  interface_ip.pure_cam = false;
732  interface_ip.pure_ram = false;
733 
734 
735  //Crossbar based interconnect for shared memory accesses, added by Syed
736  //Crossbar
737 
738  if(XML->sys.architecture==1){
739  xbar_shared = new Crossbar(coredynp.num_fpus,coredynp.num_fpus,32,&(g_tp.peri_global));//Syed: coredynp.num_fpus is used as simd_width
740  }
741  else{
742  xbar_shared = new Crossbar(coredynp.num_fpus,coredynp.num_fpus,32,&(g_tp.peri_global));//Syed: coredynp.num_fpus is used as simd_width
743  }
744 
745 
746  //TODO: Check if this line should be changed to
747  //new Crossbar(simd_width,shared_memory_banks,word_length*simd_width,&(g_tp.peri_global));
748 
749  //shared memory added by Jingwen
750  size = (int)XML->sys.core[ithCore].sharedmemory.dcache_config[0];
751  line = (int)XML->sys.core[ithCore].sharedmemory.dcache_config[1];
752  assoc = (int)XML->sys.core[ithCore].sharedmemory.dcache_config[2];
753  idx = debug?9:int(ceil(log2(size/line/assoc)));
754  tag = debug?51:XML->sys.physical_address_width-idx-int(ceil(log2(line))) + EXTRA_TAG_BITS;
755  interface_ip.specific_tag = 1;
756  interface_ip.tag_w = 1;
757  interface_ip.cache_sz = debug?32768:(int)XML->sys.core[ithCore].sharedmemory.dcache_config[0];
758  interface_ip.line_sz = debug?64:(int)XML->sys.core[ithCore].sharedmemory.dcache_config[1];
759  interface_ip.assoc = debug?8:(int)XML->sys.core[ithCore].sharedmemory.dcache_config[2];
760  interface_ip.nbanks = debug?1:(int)XML->sys.core[ithCore].sharedmemory.dcache_config[3];
761  interface_ip.out_w = interface_ip.line_sz*8;
762  interface_ip.access_mode = 0;//debug?0:XML->sys.core[ithCore].sharedmemory.dcache_config[5];
763  interface_ip.throughput = debug?1.0/clockRate:XML->sys.core[ithCore].sharedmemory.dcache_config[4]/clockRate;
764  interface_ip.latency = debug?3.0/clockRate:XML->sys.core[ithCore].sharedmemory.dcache_config[5]/clockRate;
765  interface_ip.is_cache = true;
766  interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_energy = 0;
767  interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_power = 0;
768  interface_ip.obj_func_leak_power = 0;
769  interface_ip.obj_func_cycle_t = 1;
770  interface_ip.num_rw_ports = debug?1:XML->sys.core[ithCore].memory_ports;//usually In-order has 1 and OOO has 2 at least.
771  interface_ip.num_rd_ports = 0;
772  interface_ip.num_wr_ports = 0;
773  interface_ip.num_se_rd_ports = 0;
774  sharedmemory.caches = new ArrayST(&interface_ip, "sharedmemory", Core_device, coredynp.opt_local, coredynp.core_ty);
775  sharedmemory.area.set_area(sharedmemory.area.get_area()+ sharedmemory.caches->local_result.area);
776  area.set_area(area.get_area()+ sharedmemory.caches->local_result.area + xbar_shared->area.get_area());
777 
778 
779  //shared memory buffer
780  //miss buffer
781  tag = XML->sys.physical_address_width + EXTRA_TAG_BITS;
782  data = (XML->sys.physical_address_width) + int(ceil(log2(size/line))) + sharedmemory.caches->l_ip.line_sz*8;
783  interface_ip.specific_tag = 1;
784  interface_ip.tag_w = 1;
785  interface_ip.line_sz = int(ceil(data/8.0));//int(ceil(pow(2.0,ceil(log2(data)))/8.0));
786  interface_ip.cache_sz = XML->sys.core[ithCore].sharedmemory.buffer_sizes[0]*interface_ip.line_sz;
787  interface_ip.assoc = 0;
788  interface_ip.nbanks = 1;
789  interface_ip.out_w = interface_ip.line_sz*8;
790  interface_ip.access_mode = 2;
791  interface_ip.throughput = debug?1.0/clockRate:XML->sys.core[ithCore].sharedmemory.dcache_config[4]/clockRate;
792  interface_ip.latency = debug?1.0/clockRate:XML->sys.core[ithCore].sharedmemory.dcache_config[5]/clockRate;
793  interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_energy = 0;
794  interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_power = 0;
795  interface_ip.obj_func_leak_power = 0;
796  interface_ip.obj_func_cycle_t = 1;
797  interface_ip.num_rw_ports = debug?1:XML->sys.core[ithCore].memory_ports;;
798  interface_ip.num_rd_ports = 0;
799  interface_ip.num_wr_ports = 0;
800  interface_ip.num_se_rd_ports = 0;
801  sharedmemory.missb = new ArrayST(&interface_ip, "SharedmemoryMissBuffer", Core_device, coredynp.opt_local, coredynp.core_ty);
802  sharedmemory.area.set_area(sharedmemory.area.get_area()+ sharedmemory.missb->local_result.area);
803  area.set_area(area.get_area()+ sharedmemory.missb->local_result.area);
804 
805 
806  //sharedmemory fill buffer
807  tag = XML->sys.physical_address_width + EXTRA_TAG_BITS;
808  data = sharedmemory.caches->l_ip.line_sz;
809  interface_ip.specific_tag = 1;
810  interface_ip.tag_w = 1;
811  interface_ip.line_sz = data;//int(pow(2.0,ceil(log2(data))));
812  interface_ip.cache_sz = data*XML->sys.core[ithCore].sharedmemory.buffer_sizes[1];
813  interface_ip.assoc = 0;
814  interface_ip.nbanks = 1;
815  interface_ip.out_w = interface_ip.line_sz*8;
816  interface_ip.access_mode = 2;
817  interface_ip.throughput = debug?1.0/clockRate:XML->sys.core[ithCore].sharedmemory.dcache_config[4]/clockRate;
818  interface_ip.latency = debug?1.0/clockRate:XML->sys.core[ithCore].sharedmemory.dcache_config[5]/clockRate;
819  interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_energy = 0;
820  interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_power = 0;
821  interface_ip.obj_func_leak_power = 0;
822  interface_ip.obj_func_cycle_t = 1;
823  interface_ip.num_rw_ports = debug?1:XML->sys.core[ithCore].memory_ports;;
824  interface_ip.num_rd_ports = 0;
825  interface_ip.num_wr_ports = 0;

1457 RegFU::RegFU(ParseXML* XML_interface, int ithCore_, InputParameter* interface_ip_, const CoreDynParam & dyn_p_,double exClockRate,bool exist_)
1458 :XML(XML_interface),
1459  ithCore(ithCore_),
1460  interface_ip(*interface_ip_),
1461  coredynp(dyn_p_),
1462  IRF (0),
1463  FRF (0),
1464  RFWIN (0),
1465  exist(exist_)
1466  {
1467  /*
1468  * processors have separate architectural register files for each thread.
1469  * therefore, the bypass buses need to travel across all the register files.
1470  */
1471  if (!exist) return;
1472  int data;
1473  clockRate = exClockRate;//coredynp.clockRate;
1474  executionTime = coredynp.executionTime;
1475  /*********************************************************************************
1476  * OC stage modelling (Syed Gilani)
1477  *********************************************************************************/
1478 
1479  //Crossbar
1480 
1481  if(XML->sys.architecture==1){
1482  xbar_rfu = new Crossbar(XML->sys.core[ithCore].rf_banks/2,XML->sys.core[ithCore].collector_units/2
1483  ,(128),&(g_tp.peri_global));
1484  }else{
1485  xbar_rfu = new Crossbar(XML->sys.core[ithCore].rf_banks,XML->sys.core[ithCore].collector_units
1486  ,(128),&(g_tp.peri_global));
1487  }
1488 
1489  //new Crossbar(simd_width,shared_memory_banks,word_length*simd_width,&(g_tp.peri_global));
1490 
1491  //Arbiter
1492  arbiter_rfu = new MCPAT_Arbiter(XML->sys.core[ithCore].rf_banks,XML->sys.core[ithCore].collector_units , 1,&(g_tp.peri_global));
1493 
1494 
1495 
1496  // RF banks modelled here for GPGPU-Sim (Syed Gilani)
1497  //
1498  //**********************************IRF***************************************
1499  data = coredynp.int_data_width;
1500  //data *= 8;
1501  interface_ip.is_cache = false;
1502  interface_ip.pure_cam = false;
1503  interface_ip.pure_ram = true;
1504 
1505  interface_ip.line_sz = 16;//int(ceil(data/32.0))*4 * XML->sys.core[ithCore].simd_width/4 ;//2 for Tesla as RF width half of SIMD width
1506 
1507  interface_ip.line_sz = 16;//int(ceil(data/32.0))*4 * XML->sys.core[ithCore].simd_width/2 ;//2 for Tesla as RF width half of SIMD width
1508 
1509  interface_ip.cache_sz = coredynp.num_IRF_entry*4;
1510  interface_ip.assoc = 1;
1511  interface_ip.nbanks = XML->sys.core[ithCore].rf_banks;
1512 
1513  interface_ip.out_w = interface_ip.line_sz*8;//interface_ip.line_sz*XML->sys.core[ithCore].simd_width/4; //2 for Tesla and 4 for Fermi
1514 
1515  interface_ip.out_w = interface_ip.line_sz*8;//interface_ip.line_sz*XML->sys.core[ithCore].simd_width/2; //2 for Tesla and 4 for Fermi
1516 
1517 
1518  interface_ip.access_mode = 1;
1519  interface_ip.throughput = 1/(clockRate);
1520  interface_ip.latency = 8.0/(clockRate);
1521  interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_energy = 0;
1522  interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_power = 0;
1523  interface_ip.obj_func_leak_power = 1;
1524  interface_ip.obj_func_cycle_t = 0;

1526  interface_ip.num_rd_ports = 1;//2*coredynp.peak_issueW;
1527  interface_ip.num_wr_ports = 1;//coredynp.peak_issueW;
1528  interface_ip.num_se_rd_ports = 0;

1530

1532 
1533

1535  + xbar_rfu->area.get_area() + arbiter_rfu->area.get_area());
1536  if(XML->sys.architecture==1){
1537  IRF->local_result.power.readOp.dynamic *= .33;
1538  IRF->local_result.power.writeOp.dynamic *= .33;
1539  }
1540  else {
1541  IRF->local_result.power.readOp.dynamic *= .55;
1542  IRF->local_result.power.writeOp.dynamic *= .55;
1543  }
1544 
1545 
1546 
1547 
1551  data = 32;
1552  //data *= 8;
1553  interface_ip.is_cache = false;
1554  interface_ip.pure_cam = false;
1555  interface_ip.pure_ram = true;
1556 
1557  interface_ip.line_sz = 4;//int(ceil(data/32.0))*4 * XML->sys.core[ithCore].simd_width/4 ;//2 for Tesla as RF width half of SIMD width
1558 
1559  interface_ip.line_sz = 4;//int(ceil(data/32.0))*4 * XML->sys.core[ithCore].simd_width/2 ;//2 for Tesla as RF width half of SIMD width
1560 
1561  interface_ip.cache_sz = 8*4;
1562  interface_ip.assoc = 1;
1563  interface_ip.nbanks = 1;
1564

1844 RENAMINGU::RENAMINGU(ParseXML* XML_interface, int ithCore_, InputParameter* interface_ip_, const CoreDynParam & dyn_p_,bool exist_)
1845 :XML(XML_interface),
1846  ithCore(ithCore_),
1847  interface_ip(*interface_ip_),
1848  coredynp(dyn_p_),
1849  iFRAT(0),
1850  fFRAT(0),
1851  iRRAT(0),
1852  fRRAT(0),
1853  ifreeL(0),
1854  ffreeL(0),
1855  idcl(0),
1856  fdcl(0),
1857  RAHT(0),
1858  exist(exist_)
1859  {
1860  /*
1861  * Although renaming logic maybe be used in in-order processors,
1862  * McPAT assumes no renaming logic is used since the performance gain is very limited and
1863  * the only major inorder processor with renaming logic is Itainium
1864  * that is a VLIW processor and different from current McPAT's model.
1865  * physical register base OOO must have Dual-RAT architecture or equivalent structure.FRAT:FrontRAT, RRAT:RetireRAT;
1866  * i,f prefix mean int and fp
1867  * RAT for all Renaming logic, random accessible checkpointing is used, but only update when instruction retires.
1868  * FRAT will be read twice and written once per instruction;
1869  * RRAT will be write once per instruction when committing and reads out all when context switch
1870  * checkpointing is implicit
1871  * Renaming logic is duplicated for each different hardware threads
1872  *
1873  * No Dual-RAT is needed in RS-based OOO processors,
1874  * however, RAT needs to do associative search in RAT, when instruction commits and ROB release the entry,
1875  * to make sure all the renamings associated with the ROB to be released are updated at the same time.
1876  * RAM scheme has # ARchi Reg entry with each entry hold phy reg tag,
1877  * CAM scheme has # Phy Reg entry with each entry hold ARchi reg tag,
1878  *
1879  * Both RAM and CAM have same DCL
1880  */
1881  if (!exist) return;
1882  int tag, data, out_w;
1883 // interface_ip.wire_is_mat_type = 0;
1884 // interface_ip.wire_os_mat_type = 0;
1885 // interface_ip.wt = Global_30;
1886  clockRate = coredynp.clockRate;
1887  executionTime = coredynp.executionTime;
1888  if (coredynp.core_ty==OOO)
1889  {
1890  //integer pipeline
1891  if (coredynp.scheu_ty==PhysicalRegFile)
1892  {
1893  if (coredynp.rm_ty ==RAMbased)
1894  { //FRAT with global checkpointing (GCs) please see paper tech report for detailed explaintions
1895  data = 33;//int(ceil(coredynp.phy_ireg_width*(1+coredynp.globalCheckpoint)/8.0));
1896 // data = int(ceil(coredynp.phy_ireg_width/8.0));
1897  out_w = 1;//int(ceil(coredynp.phy_ireg_width/8.0));
1898  interface_ip.is_cache = false;
1899  interface_ip.pure_cam = false;
1900  interface_ip.pure_ram = true;
1901  interface_ip.line_sz = data;
1902  interface_ip.cache_sz = data*XML->sys.core[ithCore].archi_Regs_IRF_size;
1903  interface_ip.assoc = 1;
1904  interface_ip.nbanks = 1;
1905  interface_ip.out_w = out_w*8;
1906  interface_ip.access_mode = 2;
1907  interface_ip.throughput = 1.0/clockRate;
1908  interface_ip.latency = 1.0/clockRate;
1909  interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_energy = 0;
1910  interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_power = 0;
1911  interface_ip.obj_func_leak_power = 0;
1912  interface_ip.obj_func_cycle_t = 1;
1913  interface_ip.num_rw_ports = 1;//the extra one port is for GCs
1914  interface_ip.num_rd_ports = 2*coredynp.decodeW;
1915  interface_ip.num_wr_ports = coredynp.decodeW;
1916  interface_ip.num_se_rd_ports = 0;
1917  iFRAT = new ArrayST(&interface_ip, "Int FrontRAT", Core_device, coredynp.opt_local, coredynp.core_ty);
1918  iFRAT->area.set_area(iFRAT->area.get_area()+ iFRAT->local_result.area*XML->sys.core[ithCore].number_hardware_threads);
1919  area.set_area(area.get_area()+ iFRAT->area.get_area());
1920 
1921 // //RAHT According to Intel, combine GC with FRAT is very costly.
1922 // data = int(ceil(coredynp.phy_ireg_width/8.0)*coredynp.num_IRF_entry);
1923 // out_w = data;
1924 // interface_ip.is_cache = false;
1925 // interface_ip.pure_cam = false;
1926 // interface_ip.pure_ram = true;
1927 // interface_ip.line_sz = data;
1928 // interface_ip.cache_sz = data*coredynp.globalCheckpoint;
1929 // interface_ip.assoc = 1;
1930 // interface_ip.nbanks = 1;
1931 // interface_ip.out_w = out_w*8;
1932 // interface_ip.access_mode = 0;
1933 // interface_ip.throughput = 1.0/clockRate;
1934 // interface_ip.latency = 1.0/clockRate;
1935 // interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_energy = 0;
1936 // interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_power = 0;
1937 // interface_ip.obj_func_leak_power = 0;
1938 // interface_ip.obj_func_cycle_t = 1;
1939 // interface_ip.num_rw_ports = 1;//the extra one port is for GCs
1940 // interface_ip.num_rd_ports = 2*coredynp.decodeW;
1941 // interface_ip.num_wr_ports = coredynp.decodeW;

2347

2436 void BranchPredictor::computeEnergy(bool is_tdp)
2437 {
2438  if (!exist) return;
2439  double r_access;
2440  double w_access;
2441  if (is_tdp)
2442  {
2443  r_access = coredynp.predictionW*coredynp.BR_duty_cycle;
2444  w_access = 0*coredynp.BR_duty_cycle;
2445  globalBPT->stats_t.readAc.access = r_access;
2446  globalBPT->stats_t.writeAc.access = w_access;
2447  globalBPT->tdp_stats = globalBPT->stats_t;
2448 
2449  L1_localBPT->stats_t.readAc.access = r_access;
2450  L1_localBPT->stats_t.writeAc.access = w_access;
2451  L1_localBPT->tdp_stats = L1_localBPT->stats_t;
2452 
2453  L2_localBPT->stats_t.readAc.access = r_access;
2454  L2_localBPT->stats_t.writeAc.access = w_access;
2455  L2_localBPT->tdp_stats = L2_localBPT->stats_t;
2456 
2457  chooser->stats_t.readAc.access = r_access;
2458  chooser->stats_t.writeAc.access = w_access;
2459  chooser->tdp_stats = chooser->stats_t;
2460 
2461  RAS->stats_t.readAc.access = r_access;
2462  RAS->stats_t.writeAc.access = w_access;
2463  RAS->tdp_stats = RAS->stats_t;
2464  }
2465  else
2466  {
2467  //The resolution of BPT accesses is coarse, but this is
2468  //because most simulators cannot track finer grained details
2469  r_access = XML->sys.core[ithCore].branch_instructions;
2470  w_access = XML->sys.core[ithCore].branch_mispredictions + 0.1*XML->sys.core[ithCore].branch_instructions;//10% of BR will flip internal bits//0
2471  globalBPT->stats_t.readAc.access = r_access;
2472  globalBPT->stats_t.writeAc.access = w_access;
2473  globalBPT->rtp_stats = globalBPT->stats_t;
2474 
2475  L1_localBPT->stats_t.readAc.access = r_access;
2476  L1_localBPT->stats_t.writeAc.access = w_access;
2477  L1_localBPT->rtp_stats = L1_localBPT->stats_t;
2478 
2479  L2_localBPT->stats_t.readAc.access = r_access;
2480  L2_localBPT->stats_t.writeAc.access = w_access;
2481  L2_localBPT->rtp_stats = L2_localBPT->stats_t;
2482 
2483  chooser->stats_t.readAc.access = r_access;
2484  chooser->stats_t.writeAc.access = w_access;
2485  chooser->rtp_stats = chooser->stats_t;
2486 
2487  RAS->stats_t.readAc.access = XML->sys.core[ithCore].function_calls;
2488  RAS->stats_t.writeAc.access = XML->sys.core[ithCore].function_calls;
2489  RAS->rtp_stats = RAS->stats_t;
2490  }
2491 
2492  globalBPT->power_t.reset();
2493  L1_localBPT->power_t.reset();
2494  L2_localBPT->power_t.reset();
2495  chooser->power_t.reset();
2496  RAS->power_t.reset();
2497 
2498  globalBPT->power_t.readOp.dynamic += globalBPT->local_result.power.readOp.dynamic*globalBPT->stats_t.readAc.access +
2499  globalBPT->stats_t.writeAc.access*globalBPT->local_result.power.writeOp.dynamic;
2500  L1_localBPT->power_t.readOp.dynamic += L1_localBPT->local_result.power.readOp.dynamic*L1_localBPT->stats_t.readAc.access +
2501  L1_localBPT->stats_t.writeAc.access*L1_localBPT->local_result.power.writeOp.dynamic;
2502 
2503  L2_localBPT->power_t.readOp.dynamic += L2_localBPT->local_result.power.readOp.dynamic*L2_localBPT->stats_t.readAc.access +
2504  L2_localBPT->stats_t.writeAc.access*L2_localBPT->local_result.power.writeOp.dynamic;
2505 
2506  chooser->power_t.readOp.dynamic += chooser->local_result.power.readOp.dynamic*chooser->stats_t.readAc.access +
2507  chooser->stats_t.writeAc.access*chooser->local_result.power.writeOp.dynamic;
2508  RAS->power_t.readOp.dynamic += RAS->local_result.power.readOp.dynamic*RAS->stats_t.readAc.access +
2509  RAS->stats_t.writeAc.access*RAS->local_result.power.writeOp.dynamic;
2510 
2511  if (is_tdp)
2512  {
2513  globalBPT->power = globalBPT->power_t + globalBPT->local_result.power*pppm_lkg;
2514  L1_localBPT->power = L1_localBPT->power_t + L1_localBPT->local_result.power*pppm_lkg;
2515  L2_localBPT->power = L2_localBPT->power_t + L2_localBPT->local_result.power*pppm_lkg;
2516  chooser->power = chooser->power_t + chooser->local_result.power*pppm_lkg;
2517  RAS->power = RAS->power_t + RAS->local_result.power*coredynp.pppm_lkg_multhread;
2518 
2519  power = power + globalBPT->power + L1_localBPT->power + chooser->power + RAS->power;
2520  }
2521  else
2522  {
2523  globalBPT->rt_power = globalBPT->power_t + globalBPT->local_result.power*pppm_lkg;
2524  L1_localBPT->rt_power = L1_localBPT->power_t + L1_localBPT->local_result.power*pppm_lkg;
2525  L2_localBPT->rt_power = L2_localBPT->power_t + L2_localBPT->local_result.power*pppm_lkg;
2526  chooser->rt_power = chooser->power_t + chooser->local_result.power*pppm_lkg;
2527  RAS->rt_power = RAS->power_t + RAS->local_result.power*coredynp.pppm_lkg_multhread;
2528  rt_power = rt_power + globalBPT->rt_power + L1_localBPT->rt_power + chooser->rt_power + RAS->rt_power;
2529  }
2530 }

2601 void InstFetchU::computeEnergy(bool is_tdp)
2602 {
2603  executionTime=XML->sys.total_cycles/(XML->sys.target_core_clockrate*1e6);//Syed
2604  //cout <<"IFU: execution time: "<<XML->sys.total_cycles/(XML->sys.target_core_clockrate*1e6)<<endl;
2605  //cout <<"IFU: total cycles"<<XML->sys.total_cycles<<endl;

2607  if (is_tdp)
2608  {

2611  icache.caches->stats_t.readAc.miss = 0;

2613  icache.caches->tdp_stats = icache.caches->stats_t;
2614

2641  ID_misc->tdp_stats = ID_misc->stats_t;

2660  //cout<<endl<<"inside mcpat read hit= "<<icache.caches->stats_t.readAc.hit<<endl;

2703  //icache.caches->stats_t.readAc.miss*icache.caches->local_result.tag_array2->power.readOp.dynamic+
2704  icache.caches->stats_t.readAc.miss*icache.caches->local_result.power.readOp.dynamic+ //assume tag data accessed in parallel
2705  icache.caches->stats_t.readAc.miss*icache.caches->local_result.power.writeOp.dynamic); //read miss in Icache cause a write to Icache
2706  icache.power_t.readOp.dynamic += icache.missb->stats_t.readAc.access*icache.missb->local_result.power.searchOp.dynamic +
2707  icache.missb->stats_t.writeAc.access*icache.missb->local_result.power.writeOp.dynamic;//each access to missb involves a CAM and a write
2708  icache.power_t.readOp.dynamic += icache.ifb->stats_t.readAc.access*icache.ifb->local_result.power.searchOp.dynamic +
2709  icache.ifb->stats_t.writeAc.access*icache.ifb->local_result.power.writeOp.dynamic;
2710  icache.power_t.readOp.dynamic += icache.prefetchb->stats_t.readAc.access*icache.prefetchb->local_result.power.searchOp.dynamic +
2711  icache.prefetchb->stats_t.writeAc.access*icache.prefetchb->local_result.power.writeOp.dynamic;
2712  //cout<<"Icache power: "<<icache.power_t.readOp.dynamic <<endl;
2713  IB->power_t.readOp.dynamic += IB->local_result.power.readOp.dynamic*IB->stats_t.readAc.access +
2714  IB->stats_t.writeAc.access*IB->local_result.power.writeOp.dynamic;
2715  //cout << "IB power: "<<IB->power_t.readOp.dynamic<<endl;
2716  if (coredynp.predictionW>0)
2717  {
2718  BTB->power_t.readOp.dynamic += BTB->local_result.power.readOp.dynamic*BTB->stats_t.readAc.access +
2719  BTB->stats_t.writeAc.access*BTB->local_result.power.writeOp.dynamic;
2720 
2721  BPT->computeEnergy(is_tdp);
2722  }
2723 
2724  if (is_tdp)
2725  {
2726 // icache.power = icache.power_t +
2727 // (icache.caches->local_result.power)*pppm_lkg +
2728 // (icache.missb->local_result.power +
2729 // icache.ifb->local_result.power +
2730 // icache.prefetchb->local_result.power)*pppm_Isub;
2731  icache.power = icache.power_t +
2732  (icache.caches->local_result.power +
2733  icache.missb->local_result.power +
2734  icache.ifb->local_result.power +
2735  icache.prefetchb->local_result.power)*pppm_lkg;
2736 
2737  IB->power = IB->power_t + IB->local_result.power*pppm_lkg;
2738  power = power + icache.power + IB->power;
2739  if (coredynp.predictionW>0)
2740  {
2741  BTB->power = BTB->power_t + BTB->local_result.power*pppm_lkg;
2742  power = power + BTB->power + BPT->power;
2743  }
2744 
2745  ID_inst->power_t.readOp.dynamic = ID_inst->power.readOp.dynamic;
2746  ID_operand->power_t.readOp.dynamic = ID_operand->power.readOp.dynamic;
2747  ID_misc->power_t.readOp.dynamic = ID_misc->power.readOp.dynamic;
2748 
2749  ID_inst->power.readOp.dynamic *= ID_inst->tdp_stats.readAc.access;
2750  ID_operand->power.readOp.dynamic *= ID_operand->tdp_stats.readAc.access;
2751  ID_misc->power.readOp.dynamic *= ID_misc->tdp_stats.readAc.access;
2752 
2753  power = power + (ID_inst->power +
2754  ID_operand->power +
2755  ID_misc->power);
2756  } /* if (is_tdp) */
2757  else
2758  {
2759 // icache.rt_power = icache.power_t +
2760 // (icache.caches->local_result.power)*pppm_lkg +
2761 // (icache.missb->local_result.power +
2762 // icache.ifb->local_result.power +
2763 // icache.prefetchb->local_result.power)*pppm_Isub;
2764 
2765  icache.rt_power = icache.power_t +
2766  (icache.caches->local_result.power +
2767  icache.missb->local_result.power +
2768  icache.ifb->local_result.power +
2769  icache.prefetchb->local_result.power)*pppm_lkg;
2770 
2771  //IB->rt_power = IB->power_t + IB->local_result.power*pppm_lkg;
2772  IB->rt_power.readOp.dynamic = IB->local_result.power.readOp.dynamic * IB->rtp_stats.readAc.access;
2773  IB->rt_power.readOp.dynamic += IB->local_result.power.writeOp.dynamic * IB->rtp_stats.writeAc.access;
2774  rt_power = rt_power + icache.rt_power + IB->rt_power;
2775  if (coredynp.predictionW>0)
2776  {
2777  BTB->rt_power = BTB->power_t + BTB->local_result.power*pppm_lkg;
2778  rt_power = rt_power + BTB->rt_power + BPT->rt_power;
2779  }
2780 
2781  ID_inst->rt_power.readOp.dynamic = ID_inst->power_t.readOp.dynamic*ID_inst->rtp_stats.readAc.access;
2782  ID_operand->rt_power.readOp.dynamic = ID_operand->power_t.readOp.dynamic * ID_operand->rtp_stats.readAc.access;
2783  ID_misc->rt_power.readOp.dynamic = ID_misc->power_t.readOp.dynamic * ID_misc->rtp_stats.readAc.access;
2784 
2785  rt_power = rt_power + (ID_inst->rt_power +
2786  ID_operand->rt_power +
2787  ID_misc->rt_power);
2788  //cout<<"ID inst: "<<ID_inst->rt_power.readOp.dynamic << " ID operand: "<<ID_operand->rt_power.readOp.dynamic<<" ID misc: "<<ID_misc->rt_power.readOp.dynamic<<endl;
2789  }
2790 }

2792 void InstFetchU::displayEnergy(uint32_t indent,int plevel,bool is_tdp)
2793 {
2794  if (!exist) return;
2795  string indent_str(indent, ' ');

2798

2800  if (is_tdp)
2801  {
2802

2847  ID_operand->area.get_area() +

2884 
2885 void RENAMINGU::computeEnergy(bool is_tdp)
2886 {
2887  if (!exist) return;
2888  double pppm_t[4] = {1,1,1,1};
2889  if (is_tdp)
2890  {//init stats for Peak
2891  if (coredynp.core_ty==OOO){
2892  if (coredynp.scheu_ty==PhysicalRegFile)
2893  {
2894  if (coredynp.rm_ty ==RAMbased)
2895  {
2896  iFRAT->stats_t.readAc.access = iFRAT->l_ip.num_rd_ports;
2897  iFRAT->stats_t.writeAc.access = iFRAT->l_ip.num_wr_ports;
2898  iFRAT->tdp_stats = iFRAT->stats_t;
2899 
2900  fFRAT->stats_t.readAc.access = fFRAT->l_ip.num_rd_ports;
2901  fFRAT->stats_t.writeAc.access = fFRAT->l_ip.num_wr_ports;
2902  fFRAT->tdp_stats = fFRAT->stats_t;
2903 
2904  }
2905  else if ((coredynp.rm_ty ==CAMbased))
2906  {
2907  iFRAT->stats_t.readAc.access = iFRAT->l_ip.num_search_ports;
2908  iFRAT->stats_t.writeAc.access = iFRAT->l_ip.num_wr_ports;
2909  iFRAT->tdp_stats = iFRAT->stats_t;
2910 
2911  fFRAT->stats_t.readAc.access = fFRAT->l_ip.num_search_ports;
2912  fFRAT->stats_t.writeAc.access = fFRAT->l_ip.num_wr_ports;
2913  fFRAT->tdp_stats = fFRAT->stats_t;
2914  }
2915 
2916  iRRAT->stats_t.readAc.access = iRRAT->l_ip.num_rd_ports;
2917  iRRAT->stats_t.writeAc.access = iRRAT->l_ip.num_wr_ports;
2918  iRRAT->tdp_stats = iRRAT->stats_t;
2919 
2920  fRRAT->stats_t.readAc.access = fRRAT->l_ip.num_rd_ports;
2921  fRRAT->stats_t.writeAc.access = fRRAT->l_ip.num_wr_ports;
2922  fRRAT->tdp_stats = fRRAT->stats_t;
2923 
2924  ifreeL->stats_t.readAc.access = coredynp.decodeW;//ifreeL->l_ip.num_rd_ports;;
2925  ifreeL->stats_t.writeAc.access = coredynp.decodeW;//ifreeL->l_ip.num_wr_ports;
2926  ifreeL->tdp_stats = ifreeL->stats_t;
2927 
2928  ffreeL->stats_t.readAc.access = coredynp.decodeW;//ffreeL->l_ip.num_rd_ports;
2929  ffreeL->stats_t.writeAc.access = coredynp.decodeW;//ffreeL->l_ip.num_wr_ports;
2930  ffreeL->tdp_stats = ffreeL->stats_t;
2931  }
2932  else if (coredynp.scheu_ty==ReservationStation){
2933  if (coredynp.rm_ty ==RAMbased)
2934  {
2935  iFRAT->stats_t.readAc.access = iFRAT->l_ip.num_rd_ports;
2936  iFRAT->stats_t.writeAc.access = iFRAT->l_ip.num_wr_ports;
2937  iFRAT->stats_t.searchAc.access = iFRAT->l_ip.num_search_ports;
2938  iFRAT->tdp_stats = iFRAT->stats_t;
2939 
2940  fFRAT->stats_t.readAc.access = fFRAT->l_ip.num_rd_ports;
2941  fFRAT->stats_t.writeAc.access = fFRAT->l_ip.num_wr_ports;
2942  fFRAT->stats_t.searchAc.access = fFRAT->l_ip.num_search_ports;
2943  fFRAT->tdp_stats = fFRAT->stats_t;
2944 
2945  }
2946  else if ((coredynp.rm_ty ==CAMbased))
2947  {
2948  iFRAT->stats_t.readAc.access = iFRAT->l_ip.num_search_ports;
2949  iFRAT->stats_t.writeAc.access = iFRAT->l_ip.num_wr_ports;
2950  iFRAT->tdp_stats = iFRAT->stats_t;
2951 
2952  fFRAT->stats_t.readAc.access = fFRAT->l_ip.num_search_ports;
2953  fFRAT->stats_t.writeAc.access = fFRAT->l_ip.num_wr_ports;
2954  fFRAT->tdp_stats = fFRAT->stats_t;
2955  }
2956  //Unified free list for both int and fp
2957  ifreeL->stats_t.readAc.access = coredynp.decodeW;//ifreeL->l_ip.num_rd_ports;
2958  ifreeL->stats_t.writeAc.access = coredynp.decodeW;//ifreeL->l_ip.num_wr_ports;
2959  ifreeL->tdp_stats = ifreeL->stats_t;
2960  }
2961  idcl->stats_t.readAc.access = coredynp.decodeW;
2962  fdcl->stats_t.readAc.access = coredynp.decodeW;
2963  idcl->tdp_stats = idcl->stats_t;
2964  fdcl->tdp_stats = fdcl->stats_t;
2965  }
2966  else
2967  {
2968  if (coredynp.issueW>1)
2969  {
2970  idcl->stats_t.readAc.access = coredynp.decodeW;
2971  fdcl->stats_t.readAc.access = coredynp.decodeW;
2972  idcl->tdp_stats = idcl->stats_t;
2973  fdcl->tdp_stats = fdcl->stats_t;
2974  }
2975  }
2976 
2977  }
2978  else
2979  {//init stats for Runtime Dynamic (RTP)
2980  if (coredynp.core_ty==OOO){
2981  if (coredynp.scheu_ty==PhysicalRegFile)
2982  {
2983  if (coredynp.rm_ty ==RAMbased)
2984  {
2985  iFRAT->stats_t.readAc.access = XML->sys.core[ithCore].rename_reads;
2986  iFRAT->stats_t.writeAc.access = XML->sys.core[ithCore].rename_writes;
2987  iFRAT->rtp_stats = iFRAT->stats_t;
2988 
2989  fFRAT->stats_t.readAc.access = XML->sys.core[ithCore].fp_rename_reads;
2990  fFRAT->stats_t.writeAc.access = XML->sys.core[ithCore].fp_rename_writes;
2991  fFRAT->rtp_stats = fFRAT->stats_t;
2992  }
2993  else if ((coredynp.rm_ty ==CAMbased))
2994  {
2995  iFRAT->stats_t.readAc.access = XML->sys.core[ithCore].rename_reads;
2996  iFRAT->stats_t.writeAc.access = XML->sys.core[ithCore].rename_writes;
2997  iFRAT->rtp_stats = iFRAT->stats_t;
2998 
2999  fFRAT->stats_t.readAc.access = XML->sys.core[ithCore].fp_rename_reads;
3000  fFRAT->stats_t.writeAc.access = XML->sys.core[ithCore].fp_rename_writes;
3001  fFRAT->rtp_stats = fFRAT->stats_t;
3002  }
3003 
3004  iRRAT->stats_t.readAc.access = XML->sys.core[ithCore].rename_writes;//Hack, should be (context switch + branch mispredictions)*16
3005  iRRAT->stats_t.writeAc.access = XML->sys.core[ithCore].rename_writes;
3006  iRRAT->rtp_stats = iRRAT->stats_t;
3007 
3008  fRRAT->stats_t.readAc.access = XML->sys.core[ithCore].fp_rename_writes;//Hack, should be (context switch + branch mispredictions)*16
3009  fRRAT->stats_t.writeAc.access = XML->sys.core[ithCore].fp_rename_writes;
3010  fRRAT->rtp_stats = fRRAT->stats_t;
3011 
3012  ifreeL->stats_t.readAc.access = XML->sys.core[ithCore].rename_reads;
3013  ifreeL->stats_t.writeAc.access = 2*XML->sys.core[ithCore].rename_writes;
3014  ifreeL->rtp_stats = ifreeL->stats_t;
3015 
3016  ffreeL->stats_t.readAc.access = XML->sys.core[ithCore].fp_rename_reads;
3017  ffreeL->stats_t.writeAc.access = 2*XML->sys.core[ithCore].fp_rename_writes;
3018  ffreeL->rtp_stats = ffreeL->stats_t;
3019  }
3020  else if (coredynp.scheu_ty==ReservationStation){
3021  if (coredynp.rm_ty ==RAMbased)
3022  {
3023  iFRAT->stats_t.readAc.access = XML->sys.core[ithCore].rename_reads;
3024  iFRAT->stats_t.writeAc.access = XML->sys.core[ithCore].rename_writes;
3025  iFRAT->stats_t.searchAc.access = XML->sys.core[ithCore].committed_int_instructions;//hack: not all committed instructions use regs.
3026  iFRAT->rtp_stats = iFRAT->stats_t;
3027 
3028  fFRAT->stats_t.readAc.access = XML->sys.core[ithCore].fp_rename_reads;
3029  fFRAT->stats_t.writeAc.access = XML->sys.core[ithCore].fp_rename_writes;
3030  fFRAT->stats_t.searchAc.access = XML->sys.core[ithCore].committed_fp_instructions;
3031  fFRAT->rtp_stats = fFRAT->stats_t;
3032  }
3033  else if ((coredynp.rm_ty ==CAMbased))
3034  {
3035  iFRAT->stats_t.readAc.access = XML->sys.core[ithCore].rename_reads;
3036  iFRAT->stats_t.writeAc.access = XML->sys.core[ithCore].rename_writes;
3037  iFRAT->rtp_stats = iFRAT->stats_t;
3038 
3039  fFRAT->stats_t.readAc.access = XML->sys.core[ithCore].fp_rename_reads;
3040  fFRAT->stats_t.writeAc.access = XML->sys.core[ithCore].fp_rename_writes;
3041  fFRAT->rtp_stats = fFRAT->stats_t;
3042  }
3043  //Unified free list for both int and fp since the ROB act as physcial registers
3044  ifreeL->stats_t.readAc.access = XML->sys.core[ithCore].rename_reads +
3045  XML->sys.core[ithCore].fp_rename_reads;
3046  ifreeL->stats_t.writeAc.access = 2*(XML->sys.core[ithCore].rename_writes +
3047  XML->sys.core[ithCore].fp_rename_writes);//HACK: 2-> since some of renaming in the same group
3048  //are terminated early
3049  ifreeL->rtp_stats = ifreeL->stats_t;
3050  }
3051  idcl->stats_t.readAc.access = 3*coredynp.decodeW*coredynp.decodeW*XML->sys.core[ithCore].rename_reads;
3052  fdcl->stats_t.readAc.access = 3*coredynp.fp_issueW*coredynp.fp_issueW*XML->sys.core[ithCore].fp_rename_writes;
3053  idcl->rtp_stats = idcl->stats_t;
3054  fdcl->rtp_stats = fdcl->stats_t;
3055  }
3056  else
3057  {
3058  if (coredynp.issueW>1)
3059  {
3060  idcl->stats_t.readAc.access = 2*XML->sys.core[ithCore].int_instructions;
3061  fdcl->stats_t.readAc.access = XML->sys.core[ithCore].fp_instructions;
3062  idcl->rtp_stats = idcl->stats_t;
3063  fdcl->rtp_stats = fdcl->stats_t;
3064  }
3065  }
3066 
3067  }
3068  /* Compute engine */
3069  if (coredynp.core_ty==OOO)
3070  {
3071  if (coredynp.scheu_ty==PhysicalRegFile)
3072  {
3073  if (coredynp.rm_ty ==RAMbased)
3074  {
3075  iFRAT->power_t.reset();
3076  fFRAT->power_t.reset();
3077 
3078  iFRAT->power_t.readOp.dynamic += (iFRAT->stats_t.readAc.access
3079  *(iFRAT->local_result.power.readOp.dynamic + idcl->power.readOp.dynamic)
3080  +iFRAT->stats_t.writeAc.access*iFRAT->local_result.power.writeOp.dynamic);
3081  fFRAT->power_t.readOp.dynamic += (fFRAT->stats_t.readAc.access
3082  *(fFRAT->local_result.power.readOp.dynamic + fdcl->power.readOp.dynamic)
3083  +fFRAT->stats_t.writeAc.access*fFRAT->local_result.power.writeOp.dynamic);
3084  }
3085  else if ((coredynp.rm_ty ==CAMbased))
3086  {
3087  iFRAT->power_t.reset();
3088  fFRAT->power_t.reset();
3089  iFRAT->power_t.readOp.dynamic += (iFRAT->stats_t.readAc.access
3090  *(iFRAT->local_result.power.searchOp.dynamic + idcl->power.readOp.dynamic)
3091  +iFRAT->stats_t.writeAc.access*iFRAT->local_result.power.writeOp.dynamic);
3092  fFRAT->power_t.readOp.dynamic += (fFRAT->stats_t.readAc.access
3093  *(fFRAT->local_result.power.searchOp.dynamic + fdcl->power.readOp.dynamic)
3094  +fFRAT->stats_t.writeAc.access*fFRAT->local_result.power.writeOp.dynamic);
3095  }
3096 
3097  iRRAT->power_t.reset();
3098  fRRAT->power_t.reset();
3099  ifreeL->power_t.reset();
3100  ffreeL->power_t.reset();
3101 
3102  iRRAT->power_t.readOp.dynamic += (iRRAT->stats_t.readAc.access*iRRAT->local_result.power.readOp.dynamic
3103  +iRRAT->stats_t.writeAc.access*iRRAT->local_result.power.writeOp.dynamic);
3104  fRRAT->power_t.readOp.dynamic += (fRRAT->stats_t.readAc.access*fRRAT->local_result.power.readOp.dynamic
3105  +fRRAT->stats_t.writeAc.access*fRRAT->local_result.power.writeOp.dynamic);
3106  ifreeL->power_t.readOp.dynamic += (ifreeL->stats_t.readAc.access*ifreeL->local_result.power.readOp.dynamic
3107  +ifreeL->stats_t.writeAc.access*ifreeL->local_result.power.writeOp.dynamic);
3108  ffreeL->power_t.readOp.dynamic += (ffreeL->stats_t.readAc.access*ffreeL->local_result.power.readOp.dynamic
3109  +ffreeL->stats_t.writeAc.access*ffreeL->local_result.power.writeOp.dynamic);
3110 
3111  }
3112  else if (coredynp.scheu_ty==ReservationStation)
3113  {
3114  if (coredynp.rm_ty ==RAMbased)
3115  {
3116  iFRAT->power_t.reset();
3117  fFRAT->power_t.reset();
3118 
3119  iFRAT->power_t.readOp.dynamic += (iFRAT->stats_t.readAc.access
3120  *(iFRAT->local_result.power.readOp.dynamic + idcl->power.readOp.dynamic)
3121  +iFRAT->stats_t.writeAc.access*iFRAT->local_result.power.writeOp.dynamic
3122  +iFRAT->stats_t.searchAc.access*iFRAT->local_result.power.searchOp.dynamic);
3123  fFRAT->power_t.readOp.dynamic += (fFRAT->stats_t.readAc.access
3124  *(fFRAT->local_result.power.readOp.dynamic + fdcl->power.readOp.dynamic)
3125  +fFRAT->stats_t.writeAc.access*fFRAT->local_result.power.writeOp.dynamic
3126  +fFRAT->stats_t.searchAc.access*fFRAT->local_result.power.searchOp.dynamic);
3127  }
3128  else if ((coredynp.rm_ty ==CAMbased))
3129  {
3130  iFRAT->power_t.reset();
3131  fFRAT->power_t.reset();
3132  iFRAT->power_t.readOp.dynamic += (iFRAT->stats_t.readAc.access
3133  *(iFRAT->local_result.power.searchOp.dynamic + idcl->power.readOp.dynamic)
3134  +iFRAT->stats_t.writeAc.access*iFRAT->local_result.power.writeOp.dynamic);
3135  fFRAT->power_t.readOp.dynamic += (fFRAT->stats_t.readAc.access
3136  *(fFRAT->local_result.power.searchOp.dynamic + fdcl->power.readOp.dynamic)
3137  +fFRAT->stats_t.writeAc.access*fFRAT->local_result.power.writeOp.dynamic);
3138  }
3139  ifreeL->power_t.reset();
3140  ifreeL->power_t.readOp.dynamic += (ifreeL->stats_t.readAc.access*ifreeL->local_result.power.readOp.dynamic
3141  +ifreeL->stats_t.writeAc.access*ifreeL->local_result.power.writeOp.dynamic);
3142  }
3143 
3144  }
3145  else
3146  {
3147  if (coredynp.issueW>1)
3148  {
3149  idcl->power_t.reset();
3150  fdcl->power_t.reset();
3151  set_pppm(pppm_t, idcl->stats_t.readAc.access, coredynp.num_hthreads, coredynp.num_hthreads, idcl->stats_t.readAc.access);
3152  idcl->power_t = idcl->power * pppm_t;
3153  set_pppm(pppm_t, fdcl->stats_t.readAc.access, coredynp.num_hthreads, coredynp.num_hthreads, idcl->stats_t.readAc.access);
3154  fdcl->power_t = fdcl->power * pppm_t;
3155  }
3156 
3157  }
3158 
3159  //assign value to tpd and rtp
3160  if (is_tdp)
3161  {
3162  if (coredynp.core_ty==OOO)
3163  {
3164  if (coredynp.scheu_ty==PhysicalRegFile)
3165  {
3166  iFRAT->power = iFRAT->power_t + (iFRAT->local_result.power ) * coredynp.pppm_lkg_multhread + idcl->power_t;
3167  fFRAT->power = fFRAT->power_t + (fFRAT->local_result.power ) * coredynp.pppm_lkg_multhread + fdcl->power_t;
3168  iRRAT->power = iRRAT->power_t + iRRAT->local_result.power * coredynp.pppm_lkg_multhread;
3169  fRRAT->power = fRRAT->power_t + fRRAT->local_result.power * coredynp.pppm_lkg_multhread;
3170  ifreeL->power = ifreeL->power_t + ifreeL->local_result.power * coredynp.pppm_lkg_multhread;
3171  ffreeL->power = ffreeL->power_t + ffreeL->local_result.power * coredynp.pppm_lkg_multhread;
3172  power = power + (iFRAT->power + fFRAT->power)
3173  + (iRRAT->power + fRRAT->power)
3174  + (ifreeL->power + ffreeL->power);
3175  }
3176  else if (coredynp.scheu_ty==ReservationStation)
3177  {
3178  iFRAT->power = iFRAT->power_t + (iFRAT->local_result.power ) * coredynp.pppm_lkg_multhread + idcl->power_t;
3179  fFRAT->power = fFRAT->power_t + (fFRAT->local_result.power ) * coredynp.pppm_lkg_multhread + fdcl->power_t;
3180  ifreeL->power = ifreeL->power_t + ifreeL->local_result.power * coredynp.pppm_lkg_multhread;
3181  power = power + (iFRAT->power + fFRAT->power)
3182  + ifreeL->power;
3183  }
3184  }
3185  else
3186  {
3187  power = power + idcl->power_t + fdcl->power_t;
3188  }
3189 
3190  }
3191  else
3192  {
3193  if (coredynp.core_ty==OOO)
3194  {
3195  if (coredynp.scheu_ty==PhysicalRegFile)
3196  {
3197  iFRAT->rt_power = iFRAT->power_t + (iFRAT->local_result.power ) * coredynp.pppm_lkg_multhread + idcl->power_t;
3198  fFRAT->rt_power = fFRAT->power_t + (fFRAT->local_result.power ) * coredynp.pppm_lkg_multhread + fdcl->power_t;
3199  iRRAT->rt_power = iRRAT->power_t + iRRAT->local_result.power * coredynp.pppm_lkg_multhread;
3200  fRRAT->rt_power = fRRAT->power_t + fRRAT->local_result.power * coredynp.pppm_lkg_multhread;
3201  ifreeL->rt_power = ifreeL->power_t + ifreeL->local_result.power * coredynp.pppm_lkg_multhread;
3202  ffreeL->rt_power = ffreeL->power_t + ffreeL->local_result.power * coredynp.pppm_lkg_multhread;
3203  rt_power = rt_power + (iFRAT->rt_power + fFRAT->rt_power)
3204  + (iRRAT->rt_power + fRRAT->rt_power)
3205  + (ifreeL->rt_power + ffreeL->rt_power);
3206  }
3207  else if (coredynp.scheu_ty==ReservationStation)
3208  {
3209  iFRAT->rt_power = iFRAT->power_t + (iFRAT->local_result.power ) * coredynp.pppm_lkg_multhread + idcl->power_t;
3210  fFRAT->rt_power = fFRAT->power_t + (fFRAT->local_result.power ) * coredynp.pppm_lkg_multhread + fdcl->power_t;
3211  ifreeL->rt_power = ifreeL->power_t + ifreeL->local_result.power * coredynp.pppm_lkg_multhread;
3212  rt_power = rt_power + (iFRAT->rt_power + fFRAT->rt_power)
3213  + ifreeL->rt_power;
3214  }
3215  }
3216  else
3217  {
3218  rt_power = rt_power + idcl->power_t + fdcl->power_t;
3219  }
3220 
3221  }
3222 }
